The paper discusses a problem formulation for separating moving objects from the background, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The problem formulation is based on decomposition into low-rank plus sparse matrices, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses optimization problems and solvers, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IT.
